Package: MVSMF
Version: 1.0.0
Maintainer: mgrossmann
Depends: MINIZIP HTTPD
Homepage: https://github.com/mvslovers/mvsmf
Description: z/OSMF REST API for MVS 3.8J

This is mvslovers/mvsmf: an implementation of the z/OSMF REST API
for MVS 3.8j. It lets modern clients -- Zowe Explorer for VS Code
and JetBrains IDEs, and the Zowe CLI -- work with datasets, PDS
members, jobs, USS (UFS) files and the system console on a classic
MVS host through the standard z/OSMF endpoints.

MVSMF runs as a CGI module hosted by the HTTPD server (4.0 or
later) and is loaded from HTTPD's STEPLIB. This package IEBCOPYs
the MVSMF load module into HTTPD.LINKLIB -- the same linklib HTTPD
runs from -- so the HTTPD package must be installed first. Note:
reinstalling HTTPD recreates HTTPD.LINKLIB, so reinstall MVSMF
afterwards.

The default SYS2.PARMLIB(HTTPPRM0) shipped with HTTPD 4.0 already
routes MOD=MVSMF /zosmf/*. After installing, restart the server
('/P HTTPD' then '/S HTTPD') and the API is live at
http://your-host:8080/zosmf/info. See the homepage's
docs/endpoints/ for the full endpoint reference and docs/examples.md
for curl and Zowe CLI examples.
